modules.description: This module implements a window buffer for managing fixed-size data chunks, typically used in streaming or packet processing scenarios. It provides operations to create a new window buffer and check if it has reached capacity. The window works with generic metadata types and is suited for applications like network data aggregation or batch processing.

This module handles memory-mapped file access and indexing for versioned data stores, providing direct operations to map file regions into memory and build indexed references. It works with file descriptors, bigstrings, and custom data structures for tracking object offsets, CRCs, and sizes. Concrete use cases include verifying and reconstructing Git-like pack files, streaming delta-encoded data, and managing memory-efficient object storage with configurable caching and threading.
